Table B: The following procedure codes below should be billed for select influenza vaccines for ages
two years of age and over; pneumococcal and meningococcal vaccines for 18 years of age and over;
and zoster for 50 years of age and over.

Consistent with current policy, non-invasive
prenatal trisomy screening will continue to be covered when at least one of the following criteria is met:
• either parent has a family history of aneuploidy in a 1st* or 2nd** degree relative;
• standard serum screening or fetal ultrasonographic findings indicate an increased risk of aneuploidy;
• parent(s) have a history of a previous pregnancy with a trisomy; and/or
• either parent is known to have a Robertsonian translocation.
